From cou.: 14 The potential parameters, listed in Table 1, were derived by Lewis and Catlow,35 for formal charges of Mg2+ and O2−. As will be described below, we have also used this potential to study clusters with charges varying between ±1 and ±2. Because we have not reparametrized the potential upon changing the ion charges, the energies of the clusters cannot be directly compared for different charges and we will therefore concentrate on qualitative changes in structures of the global minimum structures. It should be noted that, because of the small size of the cations, there are no repulsive Mg2+–Mg2+ (or Mg+–Mg+) Born–Mayer terms.
From Soup: 14 The potential parameters, listed in Table 1 , were derived by Lewis and Catlow, 35 for formal charges of Mg 2+ and O 2− . As will be described below, we have also used this potential to study clusters with charges varying between ±1 and ±2. Because we have not reparametrized the potential upon changing the ion charges, the energies of the clusters cannot be directly compared for different charges and we will therefore concentrate on qualitative changes in structures of the global minimum structures. It should be noted that, because of the small size of the cations , there are no repulsive Mg 2+ –Mg 2+ (or Mg + –Mg + ) Born–Mayer terms.
