From Soup: 54 The geometry of the N = 10 MgO cluster opens out from the 5 × 2 × 2 lattice to a cage structure on increasing the charge, these structures are shown in Fig. 12 . The 5 × 2 × 2 structure is reported as the lowest energy structure by de la Puente et al. at both the HF and the CHF level, though there is an error in the figure, with adjacent ions of the same type being indicated. The lowest energy structure found for (MgO) 10 by Recio et al. is also the 5 × 2 × 2 cuboid.
