From Soup: 55 The geometries of the N = 11 clusters from the rigid ion model are shown in Fig. 13 . The cluster formed for charges of 1.2 and less has a fused cuboidal-hexagonal structure. The geometry of the cluster formed when the charges are 1.3 and higher is that of a cage formed from MgO squares and hexagons. The low charge cluster is predicted by de la Puente to be the ground state configuration using both the HF and CHF methods, while Recio et al. predict a stepped cuboidal structure to be lowest in energy.
