From cou.: 56 The geometries of the N=11 clusters from the rigid ion model are shown in Fig. 13. The cluster formed for charges of 1.2 and less has a fused cuboidal-hexagonal structure. The geometry of the cluster formed when the charges are 1.3 and higher is that of a cage formed from MgO squares and hexagons. The low charge cluster is predicted by de la Puente to be the ground state configuration using both the HF and CHF methods, while Recio et al. predict a stepped cuboidal structure to be lowest in energy.
From Soup: 56 The three different structures found by the GA for N = 12 MgO clusters are shown in Fig. 14 . The structure found when the charges are equal to 1.0 is a 4 × 3 × 2 lattice, the structure found when the charges are between 1.1 and 1.5 consists of 4 stacked MgO hexagons and the structure found when the charge is 1.6 or higher is the pseudo-spherical truncated octahedron, formed from MgO squares and hexagons. These three different structures are the three lowest energy isomers published by de la Puente for (MgO) 12 clusters, with the truncated octahedron being the ground state configuration, for both HF and CHF calculations. The HF calculations of Recio predicted the hexagonal stack to lie lower in energy than the 4 × 3 × 2 cuboid — though they did not investigate the more spherical truncated octahedron, which was also found to be most stable by Ziemann and Castleman, within the rigid ion model, for q = 2.
